                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street officer. On the 9th of November, between one and two o'clock, I saw the prisoner on Blackfriars-bridge, and saw him take this handkerchief from a gentleman's pocket, and put it under his blue apron. I seized him by the arm, and took it from inside his flap. I lost the gentleman in the bustle of the crowd. I took the prisoner to the Compter, and found a blue handkerchief in his hat.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. - I picked that off the ground - it was all over dirt - Witness. There was no dirt on it.</p>
